1
00:00:01,761 --> 00:00:03,761
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

2
00:00:41,881 --> 00:00:45,241
WOMAN: Finally, this is where
our journey stops.

3
00:00:45,881 --> 00:00:47,001
(SIGHS)

4
00:00:48,001 --> 00:00:50,441
You're going to make this the place?

5
00:00:52,681 --> 00:00:53,681
It's time.

6
00:00:54,281 --> 00:00:55,561
You're ready, Delph.

7
00:00:56,321 --> 00:00:57,321
I don't think I am.

8
00:00:57,401 --> 00:01:01,041
Seventeen years is enough.
This is what I've trained you for.

9
00:01:01,361 --> 00:01:02,761
You call it training,

10
00:01:03,081 --> 00:01:04,601
I call it building doubt.

11
00:01:04,881 --> 00:01:06,681
Every lesson that you've given me,

12
00:01:06,761 --> 00:01:08,321
I feel like I've understood less,

13
00:01:09,201 --> 00:01:10,961
-not more.
-Which is the point.

14
00:01:11,241 --> 00:01:14,441
The more we learn,
the less we realise we know.

15
00:01:14,521 --> 00:01:16,641
This is our faith.

16
00:01:17,801 --> 00:01:19,721
This is our existence.

17
00:01:21,601 --> 00:01:23,401
The Creator would contend

18
00:01:24,041 --> 00:01:25,881
the world is not to be understood.

19
00:01:27,401 --> 00:01:29,681
Only experienced

20
00:01:29,761 --> 00:01:31,761
and built with our gift.

21
00:01:32,281 --> 00:01:33,561
Praise the Creator's will.

22
00:01:33,881 --> 00:01:36,841
Do this, Delph, and you'll shape
our world in worship.

23
00:01:37,721 --> 00:01:39,281
But if I fail...

24
00:01:40,521 --> 00:01:42,521
If Ican'tdoit
after all these years...

25
00:01:42,601 --> 00:01:44,161
Trust in yourself!

26
00:01:46,201 --> 00:01:47,281
Now, come on.

27
00:01:47,761 --> 00:01:50,521
Show me our years of walking
have not been wasted.

28
00:01:53,401 --> 00:01:56,441
Fulfil what we are, what only we can do.

29
00:02:00,161 --> 00:02:01,361
(SIGHS)

30
00:02:02,281 --> 00:02:03,721
(RUMBLING)

31
00:02:07,001 --> 00:02:08,401
(ENERGY PULSING)

32
00:02:19,641 --> 00:02:20,641
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

33
00:02:28,201 --> 00:02:29,361
WOMAN: What's happening?

34
00:02:30,241 --> 00:02:32,001
Stop, Delph. Now.

35
00:02:35,241 --> 00:02:37,081
It's not possible.

36
00:02:38,361 --> 00:02:39,521
(GASPS)

37
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:44,441
It cannot be, and yet...

38
00:02:45,761 --> 00:02:46,761
(EXHALES)

39
00:02:48,161 --> 00:02:49,761
(CREATURE BREATHING HEAVILY)

40
00:02:53,361 --> 00:02:54,361
-(ALARM BLARING)
-GRAHAM: Those systems

41
00:02:54,441 --> 00:02:55,841
are lit up like a Christmas tree.

42
00:02:55,921 --> 00:02:58,241
DOCTOR: Nine cries for help,
nine distress signals,

43
00:02:58,321 --> 00:02:59,761
all coming from the same planet.

44
00:02:59,841 --> 00:03:02,721
Not just the same planet,
the same area of the same planet.

45
00:03:03,001 --> 00:03:05,601
Now, listen,
planet of Ranskoor Av Kolos.

46
00:03:06,041 --> 00:03:07,161
Ranskoor Av what?

47
00:03:07,441 --> 00:03:10,161
Kolos. Roughly translated,
means "disintegrator of the soul.”

48
00:03:10,401 --> 00:03:11,401
Ooh, another cheery one.

49
00:03:11,481 --> 00:03:13,961
The TARDIS is reporting that the planet
is transmitting

50
00:03:14,041 --> 00:03:16,521
violent, psychotropic waves
throughout its atmosphere.

51
00:03:16,601 --> 00:03:18,281
The type of waves
that mess with your brain.

52
00:03:18,561 --> 00:03:22,321
Distort reality.
Change moods to the extreme.

53
00:03:23,281 --> 00:03:24,601
These are neural-balancers.

54
00:03:24,721 --> 00:03:27,281
So long as you're wearing one,
it should keep you immune to the waves.

55
00:03:27,361 --> 00:03:28,961
You must keep it on at all times.

56
00:03:30,041 --> 00:03:31,081
What happens if we lose them?

57
00:03:31,561 --> 00:03:32,561
Don't lose them!

58
00:03:32,841 --> 00:03:34,401
GRAHAM: And it has to be us, does it,

59
00:03:34,481 --> 00:03:35,721
answering these signals
from this planet?

60
00:03:35,801 --> 00:03:38,561
No, not at all.
But everyone else has passed them by.

61
00:03:38,961 --> 00:03:40,601
You think we should do the same?

62
00:03:40,681 --> 00:03:42,641
I've locked on to a craft
on the planet's surface.

63
00:03:43,441 --> 00:03:44,441
Here we go.

64
00:03:48,281 --> 00:03:49,721
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

65
00:04:02,601 --> 00:04:03,801
(DOOR CREAKS)

66
00:04:11,121 --> 00:04:13,321
This is one of the ships
that sent a distress signal.

67
00:04:13,681 --> 00:04:15,201
It looks pretty abandoned now.

68
00:04:16,641 --> 00:04:18,081
Cryo-sleep chambers.

69
00:04:19,521 --> 00:04:22,201
Long-range craft. Weapons archive.

70
00:04:24,001 --> 00:04:26,321
Been in service for a long time
by the looks of things.

71
00:04:27,521 --> 00:04:29,441
Who sent the signal? Where's the crew?

72
00:04:30,241 --> 00:04:31,241
Doctor.

73
00:04:32,761 --> 00:04:34,081
(GASPS)

74
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:42,201
-DOCTOR: Hi.
-Who are you?

75
00:04:43,361 --> 00:04:44,481
I'm the Doctor.

76
00:04:45,081 --> 00:04:46,081
This is Yaz,

77
00:04:46,401 --> 00:04:47,881
Ryan, and Graham.

78
00:04:49,201 --> 00:04:50,401
What is that thing?

79
00:04:51,121 --> 00:04:52,201
It's what we travel in.

80
00:04:52,761 --> 00:04:56,361
See? The sign on the front,
we respond to urgent calls.

81
00:04:57,201 --> 00:04:58,561
You look like an urgent call.

82
00:05:01,561 --> 00:05:02,561
What's your name?

83
00:05:02,761 --> 00:05:03,921
Did they send you?

84
00:05:05,681 --> 00:05:08,041
When you say "they," who do you mean?

85
00:05:09,161 --> 00:05:10,201
People from here?

86
00:05:10,561 --> 00:05:12,361
Because we've just arrived here,
remember?

87
00:05:12,681 --> 00:05:14,281
We've never been to this planet before.

88
00:05:14,361 --> 00:05:17,081
So we can't be with them,
whoever they are.

89
00:05:18,961 --> 00:05:20,081
That's right.

90
00:05:23,081 --> 00:05:26,281
Now, is it just you,
or is there any other crew with you?

91
00:05:28,521 --> 00:05:29,561
I don't know.

92
00:05:33,801 --> 00:05:34,801
What's happened to me?

93
00:05:38,041 --> 00:05:40,481
My friends are going to take a look
around your ship if that's okay?

94
00:05:41,721 --> 00:05:43,081
See what you can find out.

95
00:05:47,001 --> 00:05:48,001
I should have left.

96
00:05:49,441 --> 00:05:50,961
And why haven't you?

97
00:05:54,201 --> 00:05:55,521
I can't remember my name.

98
00:05:58,681 --> 00:06:02,281
I used to know before I went outside.
I should never have gone outside.

99
00:06:02,881 --> 00:06:05,281
Why? What happened outside?

100
00:06:06,441 --> 00:06:07,481
The battle.

101
00:06:07,721 --> 00:06:08,801
(BREATH TREMBLING)

102
00:06:11,881 --> 00:06:14,081
Who are you? How did you get here?

103
00:06:15,681 --> 00:06:16,801
We've just been talking.

104
00:06:18,281 --> 00:06:19,441
We just arrived.

105
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:21,041
(BREATH TREMBLING)

106
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:22,881
We want to help you.

107
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:26,041
I think this planet is having
a bad effect on you.

108
00:06:26,881 --> 00:06:28,361
Would you consider putting this on?

109
00:06:29,441 --> 00:06:30,921
Neural-balancer.

110
00:06:31,001 --> 00:06:32,521
It'll help calm your mind.

111
00:06:33,161 --> 00:06:34,161
Please.

112
00:06:36,241 --> 00:06:37,241
(BREATH TREMBLING)

113
00:06:38,201 --> 00:06:39,521
Put this on.

114
00:06:43,521 --> 00:06:44,721
YASMIN: I think I found an on button.

115
00:06:45,161 --> 00:06:46,161
(WHIRRING)

116
00:06:49,001 --> 00:06:51,081
(WHISPERING) Who do you think
that lot are, then?

117
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:52,601
I think this is the rest of them.

118
00:06:53,081 --> 00:06:54,521
So there's four in total.

119
00:06:55,121 --> 00:06:56,161
He's the commander.

120
00:06:58,321 --> 00:07:00,001
RYAN: Maybe he killed his own crew.

121
00:07:00,161 --> 00:07:02,161
GRAHAM: Always one for
the cheery option.

122
00:07:02,921 --> 00:07:05,001
YASMIN: We don't know they're dead.
All we know is they're not here.

123
00:07:05,081 --> 00:07:06,081
RYAN: Yeah.

124
00:07:06,161 --> 00:07:08,001
He's taken a neural-balancer.

125
00:07:08,521 --> 00:07:10,401
I'm hoping it'll restore
something in his mind.

126
00:07:11,081 --> 00:07:12,761
He looks pretty broken to me, Doc.

127
00:07:14,361 --> 00:07:15,441
(DEVICE BLEEPING)

128
00:07:15,921 --> 00:07:16,921
Engine's fine.

129
00:07:17,441 --> 00:07:18,921
-(SHIP SYSTEMS POWERING UP)
-Power's still working.

130
00:07:19,001 --> 00:07:20,081
Ship's fine.

131
00:07:20,161 --> 00:07:21,681
He could have left whenever he wanted.

132
00:07:21,761 --> 00:07:22,801
It doesn't make sense.

133
00:07:23,001 --> 00:07:24,001
Here he is.

134
00:07:24,121 --> 00:07:25,401
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

135
00:07:26,161 --> 00:07:27,201
Paltraki.

136
00:07:28,961 --> 00:07:31,161
My name is Paltraki.

137
00:07:33,401 --> 00:07:34,641
Nice to meet you, Paltraki.

138
00:07:35,401 --> 00:07:36,521
Neural-balancer kicking in?

139
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:39,321
Don't push too hard.
They work slowly.

140
00:07:39,801 --> 00:07:40,801
It'll come back.

141
00:07:41,041 --> 00:07:42,201
(SHIP ALARM BLARES)

142
00:07:42,281 --> 00:07:43,361
Whoa.

143
00:07:43,521 --> 00:07:44,641
What is that?

144
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:46,761
We can answer it for you.
Do you want us to activate it?

145
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:48,081
Get out from the viewing line.

146
00:07:48,681 --> 00:07:50,161
-Do as I say, son.
-Okay.

147
00:07:51,681 --> 00:07:52,801
(STATIC)

148
00:07:53,641 --> 00:07:54,921
(MONITOR BEEPS)

149
00:07:55,001 --> 00:07:56,681
-Paltraki.
-What do you want?

150
00:07:58,521 --> 00:07:59,921
You must return to us.

151
00:08:01,161 --> 00:08:02,961
The Creator commands it.

152
00:08:03,801 --> 00:08:05,561
CREATURE: (BREATHES HEAVILY) Paltraki.

153
00:08:06,841 --> 00:08:08,241
(CREATURE CONTINUES BREATHING HEAVILY)

154
00:08:09,921 --> 00:08:12,041
Do you remember me, Paltraki?

155
00:08:13,681 --> 00:08:15,041
I know that voice.

156
00:08:16,401 --> 00:08:17,641
-Is that...
-It can't be.

157
00:08:19,721 --> 00:08:23,041
I want what is mine returned.

158
00:08:24,001 --> 00:08:25,361
(CREATURE BREATHING HEAVILY)

159
00:08:26,761 --> 00:08:28,281
And why would I do that?

160
00:08:29,681 --> 00:08:30,681
For your crew.

161
00:08:31,681 --> 00:08:33,521
Return what you took

162
00:08:34,441 --> 00:08:38,161
or I will dismantle them piece by piece

163
00:08:38,801 --> 00:08:41,361
beamed directly into your ship.

164
00:08:43,441 --> 00:08:45,361
GIRL: (OVER MONITOR)
Paltraki, don't go back.

165
00:08:45,721 --> 00:08:48,001
Don't worry about us.
You got what you came for...

166
00:08:48,201 --> 00:08:49,201
(GIRL SCREAMING)

167
00:08:54,441 --> 00:08:56,081
Two of your crew left.

168
00:08:56,401 --> 00:08:58,561
You have till nightfall.

169
00:08:59,521 --> 00:09:02,401
WOMAN: Please, return what you took.

170
00:09:02,841 --> 00:09:05,121
Do as the Creator desires.

171
00:09:07,121 --> 00:09:08,161
(GASPS)

172
00:09:09,401 --> 00:09:10,401
Is it the same one?

173
00:09:10,681 --> 00:09:11,681
I don't know.

174
00:09:11,841 --> 00:09:13,041
YASMIN: That can't be Tim Shaw.

175
00:09:13,561 --> 00:09:14,561
I thought he was dead.

176
00:09:14,641 --> 00:09:17,841
I sent him back to where he came from,
using his own recall device.

177
00:09:17,921 --> 00:09:19,001
Then why is he here?

178
00:09:21,401 --> 00:09:22,401
Who's the girl?

179
00:09:23,081 --> 00:09:24,081
Her name

180
00:09:26,201 --> 00:09:27,201
was

181
00:09:29,601 --> 00:09:30,801
Umsang.

182
00:09:32,721 --> 00:09:34,921
We fought alongside each other.

183
00:09:35,361 --> 00:09:36,681
What did you take?

184
00:09:37,401 --> 00:09:38,401
Not take.

185
00:09:40,481 --> 00:09:41,481
Recover.

186
00:09:42,961 --> 00:09:44,401
(BUZZING)

187
00:09:49,561 --> 00:09:50,561
What is it?

188
00:09:51,001 --> 00:09:52,921
Our mission is retrieval.

189
00:09:53,001 --> 00:09:54,201
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

190
00:09:57,001 --> 00:09:59,761
Great. All I'm getting
is contradictions.

191
00:10:00,881 --> 00:10:03,521
Looks mineral. Maybe it's been extracted

192
00:10:03,601 --> 00:10:04,601
from the planet.

193
00:10:04,681 --> 00:10:06,321
The density's blowing the sonic's mind.

194
00:10:06,681 --> 00:10:08,521
If it's that valuable,
they'd want to keep it safe.

195
00:10:08,601 --> 00:10:09,601
It's not just safe.

196
00:10:10,121 --> 00:10:12,361
There's an incredibly sophisticated
stasis lock

197
00:10:12,441 --> 00:10:15,601
embedded in the container's
bio structure and I don't understand it.

198
00:10:17,401 --> 00:10:18,761
Stenza technology.

199
00:10:20,001 --> 00:10:21,121
What is it, Paltraki?

200
00:10:21,201 --> 00:10:22,681
Where did it come from?

201
00:10:22,801 --> 00:10:24,841
-PALTRAKI: I mustn't return it, but...
-(DEVICE BLEEPING)

202
00:10:25,721 --> 00:10:26,841
They have my crew.

203
00:10:27,281 --> 00:10:28,841
Hey, have you seen this?

204
00:10:29,201 --> 00:10:30,481
Some kind of mapping device.

205
00:10:30,841 --> 00:10:32,121
All kinds of stuff on here.

206
00:10:32,361 --> 00:10:33,641
Targets marked on.

207
00:10:37,761 --> 00:10:40,361
Mission briefing. Was this yours?

208
00:10:41,161 --> 00:10:43,001
Maybe, I... I don't know.

209
00:10:43,441 --> 00:10:44,681
We could use it to retrace

210
00:10:44,761 --> 00:10:46,041
-where he was.
-DOCTOR: Yeah.

211
00:10:46,441 --> 00:10:48,081
We want to help you get your crew back.

212
00:10:48,641 --> 00:10:49,641
We'll go with you.

213
00:10:50,361 --> 00:10:52,441
Because we've got unfinished business
with that monster.

214
00:10:57,401 --> 00:10:58,881
Oh, I can Lift it!

215
00:10:59,121 --> 00:11:01,641
I shouldn't be able to.
How can I lift it

216
00:11:02,321 --> 00:11:04,201
with that impossible density?

217
00:11:04,281 --> 00:11:07,321
We're going to find your crew
and work out why this is so important.

218
00:11:09,001 --> 00:11:11,041
Equipment bay. Is it over there?

219
00:11:11,121 --> 00:11:12,121
Do you mind if I take a look?

220
00:11:13,441 --> 00:11:14,441
Okay, Graham?

221
00:11:17,881 --> 00:11:20,561
DOCTOR: Ranskoor Av Kolos
isn't the Stenzas' home planet

222
00:11:20,681 --> 00:11:22,801
so how can that be Tim Shaw?

223
00:11:34,881 --> 00:11:37,361
-YASMIN: Feeling sick?
-Yeah, like travel sick, but worse.

224
00:11:38,321 --> 00:11:40,201
Sickness is how it started.

225
00:11:40,441 --> 00:11:41,761
GRAHAM: So what is that sound?

226
00:11:42,001 --> 00:11:43,121
I think it's the planet.

227
00:11:43,761 --> 00:11:45,241
Obviously it doesn't like intruders.

228
00:11:46,161 --> 00:11:47,161
Doc, can I have a word?

229
00:11:47,481 --> 00:11:49,121
-Of course.
-Just the two of us.

230
00:11:50,321 --> 00:11:51,321
Fine.

231
00:11:52,321 --> 00:11:53,321
Come on, Yaz.

232
00:11:57,201 --> 00:11:58,361
I need to be honest with you,

233
00:11:58,441 --> 00:12:00,561
because I am really grateful
for everything you've done for me.

234
00:12:00,641 --> 00:12:04,401
Well, for us, everywhere we've been,
all the adventures, been amazing.

235
00:12:05,241 --> 00:12:07,401
But, if that is the creature
from Sheffield,

236
00:12:07,881 --> 00:12:09,441
I will kill it if I can.

237
00:12:11,601 --> 00:12:12,921
For what it did to Grace.

238
00:12:13,801 --> 00:12:15,001
Go back to the TARDIS, Graham.

239
00:12:15,081 --> 00:12:16,081
No.

240
00:12:16,641 --> 00:12:17,841
I won't let you do that.

241
00:12:17,921 --> 00:12:19,241
You ain't gonna have a say in it.

242
00:12:20,681 --> 00:12:21,761
You're better than this.

243
00:12:22,401 --> 00:12:24,241
You are. You have to be.

244
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:26,161
If you kill him,

245
00:12:26,241 --> 00:12:28,441
I can't have you travel with me.
That's if you even live.

246
00:12:30,121 --> 00:12:31,601
-I understand.
-No, you don't.

247
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:35,521
We're going to rescue hostages. Anything
that compromises them is dangerous.

248
00:12:35,961 --> 00:12:38,041
And if you kill him,
you become the same as him.

249
00:12:39,201 --> 00:12:40,201
I ain't having that.

250
00:12:40,841 --> 00:12:41,961
I'm serious, Graham.

251
00:12:46,561 --> 00:12:47,561
And so am I.

252
00:12:49,761 --> 00:12:52,881
RYAN: That's all you remember, being
back on your ship without your crew?

253
00:12:52,961 --> 00:12:54,041
PALTRAKI: Nothing before that.

254
00:12:54,121 --> 00:12:56,721
There's a reason I should have left.

255
00:12:57,521 --> 00:12:58,881
I can nearly remember.

256
00:12:59,521 --> 00:13:01,121
The Doctor said don't push.

257
00:13:01,401 --> 00:13:03,001
The memories will return.

258
00:13:03,401 --> 00:13:04,401
Hey, Yaz, look.

259
00:13:04,841 --> 00:13:06,001
You all seeing those?

260
00:13:12,281 --> 00:13:14,801
-What happened here?
-PALTRAKI: Those that came before us.

261
00:13:15,681 --> 00:13:17,281
That failed and fell.

262
00:13:19,121 --> 00:13:21,721
The vanquished of Ranskoor Av Kolos.

263
00:13:22,721 --> 00:13:24,801
But that's not all, look beyond.

264
00:13:26,041 --> 00:13:28,121
What are you looking at?

265
00:13:28,201 --> 00:13:29,721
Look at the mists.

266
00:13:32,161 --> 00:13:35,241
Through the battlefield,
on to the edifice.

267
00:13:35,601 --> 00:13:37,281
That was our destination.

268
00:13:38,201 --> 00:13:40,001
RYAN: We're not going
to go through that, are we?

269
00:13:40,121 --> 00:13:42,081
No one in their right mind's
gonna go through there.

270
00:14:03,321 --> 00:14:04,841
RYAN: What do you think's inside?

271
00:14:06,041 --> 00:14:08,801
DOCTOR: Other than Tim Shaw,
I don't know.

272
00:14:14,961 --> 00:14:16,241
Equipment.

273
00:14:18,961 --> 00:14:21,121
I borrowed all this
from your ship, Paltraki.

274
00:14:21,841 --> 00:14:24,201
These throat mics work like commdots.

275
00:14:24,441 --> 00:14:26,481
Side of the neck. Stay in contact.

276
00:14:27,001 --> 00:14:28,001
Take one each.

277
00:14:30,761 --> 00:14:33,761
Grenades, codebreakers
for doors... Also,

278
00:14:34,321 --> 00:14:35,321
a bomb.

279
00:14:35,481 --> 00:14:36,641
What happened to "never do weapons"?

280
00:14:36,801 --> 00:14:38,441
It's a flexible creed.

281
00:14:38,521 --> 00:14:41,761
Doors, locks, walls, buildings,
fair game.

282
00:14:42,121 --> 00:14:43,761
If it can be rebuilt, I'll allow it.

283
00:14:44,081 --> 00:14:46,041
No, no, you stopped me
trying to shoot the Sniperbots before.

284
00:14:46,161 --> 00:14:49,321
You were new. I have to lay down
the rules if someone's new.

285
00:14:49,801 --> 00:14:51,241
Also, don't quote that back to me.

286
00:14:51,681 --> 00:14:53,081
My rules change all the time.

287
00:14:54,081 --> 00:14:55,121
Be careful with them.

288
00:14:57,281 --> 00:14:58,841
You've got your trackers.
As far as I can decipher,

289
00:14:59,001 --> 00:15:00,841
the golden markers
on your devices

290
00:15:00,921 --> 00:15:02,561
relate to your
original mission purpose...

291
00:15:02,681 --> 00:15:04,641
-(DEVICE BLEEPS)
-...for Paltraki and his crew.

292
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:07,201
Which must connect to this object.

293
00:15:07,961 --> 00:15:10,921
That's where I want you both to head.
See what you can find.

294
00:15:11,281 --> 00:15:12,561
Graham, Ryan,

295
00:15:12,721 --> 00:15:14,881
you've got life signal markers
on your devices.

296
00:15:15,121 --> 00:15:16,401
Head to that area

297
00:15:16,561 --> 00:15:17,881
and rescue Paltraki's crew.

298
00:15:18,161 --> 00:15:19,921
What about you? Where are you heading?

299
00:15:20,081 --> 00:15:21,601
I'm gonna find our friend.

300
00:15:22,521 --> 00:15:23,841
I want to come with you.

301
00:15:24,721 --> 00:15:25,961
No.

302
00:15:28,721 --> 00:15:30,161
What will you do once you find him?

303
00:15:30,361 --> 00:15:33,241
Find out what this is
and why it's so precious to him.

304
00:15:33,721 --> 00:15:37,681
Oh, I might need
a bit of a negotiation leverage.

305
00:15:37,841 --> 00:15:39,241
(SIGHS)

306
00:15:40,321 --> 00:15:41,321
RYAN: What are you doing with those?

307
00:15:41,521 --> 00:15:42,521
DOCTOR: Grenades.

308
00:15:42,601 --> 00:15:44,161
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)
-As insurance policy.

309
00:15:44,681 --> 00:15:46,121
You think that's smart?

310
00:15:46,321 --> 00:15:47,441
I think it's a precaution.

311
00:15:47,881 --> 00:15:49,481
I like precautions.
Always take precautions.

312
00:15:49,641 --> 00:15:51,041
Especially when you don't know
what you're doing.

313
00:15:51,641 --> 00:15:52,881
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

314
00:16:00,681 --> 00:16:01,681
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

315
00:16:10,041 --> 00:16:11,921
DOCTOR: Ah, I should
have brought wellies.

316
00:16:12,121 --> 00:16:14,561
That could have been another precaution,
"always bring wellies."

317
00:16:14,641 --> 00:16:17,761
I love wellies.
In fact, I think I half-invented them.

318
00:16:18,521 --> 00:16:20,441
YASMIN: And you think
this is the best way in?

319
00:16:20,561 --> 00:16:23,761
DOCTOR: (PANTING) Closest thing
to a front door this building's got.

320
00:16:24,041 --> 00:16:25,201
As far as I can tell.

321
00:16:25,281 --> 00:16:26,961
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

322
00:16:27,081 --> 00:16:28,081
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER BLEEPS)

323
00:16:30,081 --> 00:16:31,961
Now.

324
00:16:32,881 --> 00:16:34,561
Doorbell.

325
00:16:36,121 --> 00:16:37,641
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRS AND BLEEPS)

326
00:16:37,721 --> 00:16:40,081
Oh, entrance activation field.

327
00:16:40,841 --> 00:16:42,521
-Maybe I can bypass...
-(ALL SCREAMING)

328
00:16:44,481 --> 00:16:46,441
(ALL PANTING)

329
00:16:47,321 --> 00:16:50,881
Whatever happened to doors?
Don't aliens bother with doors?

330
00:16:51,361 --> 00:16:54,201
-The building dragged us in.
-So they know we're here.

331
00:16:54,321 --> 00:16:56,401
Be quiet and get moving. Come on.

332
00:16:57,921 --> 00:16:59,521
You all know what you have to do.

333
00:17:04,321 --> 00:17:06,521
GRAHAM: You see anything?
RYAN: Of course I can't see anything,

334
00:17:06,601 --> 00:17:08,321
I'm looking at the same things as you.

335
00:17:09,121 --> 00:17:10,481
I know what you're thinking.

336
00:17:11,081 --> 00:17:12,481
Is that right?

337
00:17:13,761 --> 00:17:16,201
You want to get to him for Nan.
Hold that.

338
00:17:17,401 --> 00:17:18,601
Do I really?

339
00:17:18,681 --> 00:17:20,921
Why don't you just concentrate
on what we're supposed to be doing?

340
00:17:21,441 --> 00:17:23,201
You think that's what Nan would want?

341
00:17:23,321 --> 00:17:26,081
No, I think your nan
would want to be alive.

342
00:17:27,321 --> 00:17:29,961
She actually liked being alive
and she was really good at it.

343
00:17:30,761 --> 00:17:31,761
And she'd say to me,

344
00:17:31,841 --> 00:17:36,481
"Graham, if you get the chance,
you send that blue piece of rubbish

345
00:17:36,561 --> 00:17:38,321
"to kingdom come.”

346
00:17:39,081 --> 00:17:40,921
Because you know why?

347
00:17:41,081 --> 00:17:42,401
Your nan...

348
00:17:42,481 --> 00:17:45,481
(WHISPERING) Your nan
might have been kind,

349
00:17:45,561 --> 00:17:48,841
but she was also tougher
than you and me put together.

350
00:17:48,921 --> 00:17:50,561
-And what about the rest of us?
-No.

351
00:17:50,641 --> 00:17:53,761
Me, Yaz, and the Doctor.
I thought we were a team.

352
00:17:53,841 --> 00:17:56,641
Don't wreck what we've got
because you're still angry.

353
00:17:56,721 --> 00:17:57,801
I am not...

354
00:17:57,961 --> 00:18:02,241
Look, we did not get rid
of that thing properly.

355
00:18:02,321 --> 00:18:03,641
Right? And now look what's happened.

356
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,841
-Shut up.
-What, because you know I'm right?

357
00:18:07,921 --> 00:18:09,281
No, really, shut up!

358
00:18:09,561 --> 00:18:10,641
-Huh?
-Run!

359
00:18:10,761 --> 00:18:12,041
Cyberbots!

360
00:18:12,921 --> 00:18:15,241
RYAN: How did they get here?
GRAHAM: He's built an army of them!

361
00:18:15,841 --> 00:18:18,321
No, no, more of them! We're trapped!

362
00:18:19,361 --> 00:18:20,361
(PANTING)

363
00:18:21,161 --> 00:18:22,441
-(WEAPONS POWERING UP)
-(GASPS)

364
00:18:23,241 --> 00:18:24,241
Duck!

365
00:18:24,321 --> 00:18:25,321
(GASPS)

366
00:18:29,281 --> 00:18:30,961
(PANTING)

367
00:18:33,161 --> 00:18:34,841
-RYAN: Thank me later.
-(BREATHING HEAVILY)

368
00:18:35,041 --> 00:18:36,161
(BOTH WHIMPER)

369
00:18:51,081 --> 00:18:52,081
Hi.

370
00:18:53,441 --> 00:18:54,801
WOMAN: Who are you?

371
00:18:54,921 --> 00:18:56,081
DOCTOR: I'm no one.

372
00:18:56,241 --> 00:18:58,201
But I have something
you might be interested in.

373
00:18:58,641 --> 00:19:00,441
Where is the object?

374
00:19:00,921 --> 00:19:02,801
Never talk in the face of a gun.

375
00:19:02,921 --> 00:19:05,601
Point of principle. Please put it down.

376
00:19:07,921 --> 00:19:09,321
It's going to be like that, is it?

377
00:19:09,961 --> 00:19:10,961
Fine.

378
00:19:11,081 --> 00:19:12,761
I've attached
a couple of explosive devices

379
00:19:12,841 --> 00:19:14,361
to your object here on my back.

380
00:19:15,201 --> 00:19:17,761
So shoot and you jeopardise
whatever this thing is.

381
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:20,361
And what is it?

382
00:19:20,681 --> 00:19:23,081
Come on! Share with the class.

383
00:19:23,561 --> 00:19:25,081
Where is Paltraki?

384
00:19:25,201 --> 00:19:27,361
I'm not answering your questions
if you don't answer mine.

385
00:19:30,001 --> 00:19:31,921
Are his other two crew members
still alive?

386
00:19:33,281 --> 00:19:34,281
Yes.

387
00:19:34,681 --> 00:19:36,281
See, that wasn't so hard.

388
00:19:36,961 --> 00:19:39,161
And good. Thank you.

389
00:19:40,721 --> 00:19:42,761
Why didn't you stop that woman
from being killed?

390
00:19:47,561 --> 00:19:48,681
What's your name?

391
00:19:51,001 --> 00:19:55,081
I am Andinio of the Ux.

392
00:19:55,281 --> 00:19:57,401
Are you kidding, the Ux?

393
00:19:57,481 --> 00:19:59,201
As in the duo species?

394
00:19:59,441 --> 00:20:02,041
Only ever two of you?
Lifespan of millennia?

395
00:20:02,361 --> 00:20:04,561
Only found on three planets
in the whole universe.

396
00:20:04,761 --> 00:20:08,161
I've never met an Ux.
Congratulations, it must be so cool.

397
00:20:08,281 --> 00:20:09,961
Wait, there's something else.

398
00:20:12,441 --> 00:20:13,721
Oh, I can't remember.

399
00:20:15,121 --> 00:20:16,761
What happened here, Andinio?

400
00:20:16,961 --> 00:20:19,641
Make sense of it for me.
The battle zone outside?

401
00:20:20,841 --> 00:20:24,321
They came for the Creator.
We defended him.

402
00:20:24,481 --> 00:20:26,121
(GASPS) I've remembered.

403
00:20:26,401 --> 00:20:27,561
Wait.

404
00:20:28,961 --> 00:20:30,681
Is this yours, this building?

405
00:20:30,761 --> 00:20:32,241
Is it true about the Ux?

406
00:20:32,641 --> 00:20:36,201
Faith-driven dimensional engineers.

407
00:20:36,281 --> 00:20:38,361
Is that why the building feels alive?

408
00:20:39,481 --> 00:20:40,801
This is our shrine.

409
00:20:41,041 --> 00:20:43,161
It feels like an energy
running through it.

410
00:20:43,801 --> 00:20:45,801
Surrender the object and go.

411
00:20:47,601 --> 00:20:50,481
-(WEAPON POWERING UP)
-You have until the count of three.

412
00:20:51,881 --> 00:20:53,081
Show him my face.

413
00:20:54,841 --> 00:20:55,841
What?

414
00:20:55,961 --> 00:20:57,161
Let him see my face.

415
00:20:57,481 --> 00:20:59,401
Your "Creator."

416
00:20:59,721 --> 00:21:01,561
(ENERGY PULSING)

417
00:21:03,081 --> 00:21:05,321
TZIM-SHA: Bring her to me.

418
00:21:06,081 --> 00:21:07,121
But...

419
00:21:10,121 --> 00:21:12,081
How can he know you?

420
00:21:16,481 --> 00:21:19,441
PALTRAKI: Greston.
My first name is Greston.

421
00:21:19,521 --> 00:21:22,121
Just remembered. Memories reconnecting.

422
00:21:25,241 --> 00:21:26,841
What about where you're from?

423
00:21:27,881 --> 00:21:29,321
Stebble.

424
00:21:29,601 --> 00:21:30,881
"Stebble"?

425
00:21:31,401 --> 00:21:32,521
What about you?

426
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:35,441
-Earth.
-(SCOFFS)

427
00:21:35,641 --> 00:21:39,041
-What kind of a word is that?
-It's better than Stebble, mate.

428
00:21:41,321 --> 00:21:44,041
-Do you have a home there?
-Beautiful home.

429
00:21:44,641 --> 00:21:45,721
Some land

430
00:21:45,921 --> 00:21:47,241
and animals.

431
00:21:48,721 --> 00:21:50,601
Too many facts coming back. It's like

432
00:21:50,681 --> 00:21:53,281
a flood. I don't know
what's important, or...

433
00:21:54,921 --> 00:21:56,441
We were the last fleet.

434
00:21:57,801 --> 00:22:00,281
When the others didn't come back,
they sent for us.

435
00:22:01,401 --> 00:22:02,681
Who sent you?

436
00:22:03,201 --> 00:22:04,201
Why did you come?

437
00:22:06,521 --> 00:22:10,881
The Congress of the Nine Planets

438
00:22:11,601 --> 00:22:13,241
in response to the atrocities.

439
00:22:14,401 --> 00:22:15,681
Which were what?

440
00:22:16,961 --> 00:22:18,481
YASMIN: Cyberbots!

441
00:22:19,361 --> 00:22:21,641
(GASPS) Nice shot.

442
00:22:22,281 --> 00:22:24,441
They have an army of those things.

443
00:22:26,041 --> 00:22:28,841
-Why do you call him the Creator?
-ANDINIO: Our faith

444
00:22:28,921 --> 00:22:32,001
is handed down.
The Creator is the cornerstone.

445
00:22:33,001 --> 00:22:34,281
You're the first to see him.

446
00:22:34,961 --> 00:22:37,241
We are the blessed generation.

447
00:22:38,441 --> 00:22:40,841
Wait, there's only ever two of you.
Where's the other one?

448
00:22:41,721 --> 00:22:43,801
I don't have to answer
all these questions.

449
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:47,761
That's what my teachers used to say,
usually just as they quit teaching.

450
00:22:48,241 --> 00:22:50,441
I've got so many questions, Andinio,

451
00:22:50,841 --> 00:22:53,401
because there's a battlefield outside
where many people died,

452
00:22:53,481 --> 00:22:54,761
but you're no warrior.

453
00:22:54,841 --> 00:22:59,001
And your words are certain,
but your eyes are full of doubt.

454
00:23:02,601 --> 00:23:05,041
How can you know him?

455
00:23:05,961 --> 00:23:08,761
Yes, how can I?

456
00:23:14,721 --> 00:23:16,801
(DEVICES BEEPING)

457
00:23:18,081 --> 00:23:19,081
Here.

458
00:23:20,001 --> 00:23:21,121
It's here.

459
00:23:36,881 --> 00:23:38,681
YASMIN: More of those mineral samples.

460
00:23:40,361 --> 00:23:42,401
PALTRAKI: Five in total.

461
00:23:45,081 --> 00:23:46,761
I remember.

462
00:23:47,721 --> 00:23:51,481
We landed and fought our way here.

463
00:23:52,761 --> 00:23:55,881
Even though the planet
was playing with our minds,

464
00:23:57,401 --> 00:24:00,361
we never believed any of this
was possible.

465
00:24:02,201 --> 00:24:03,641
But it was.

466
00:24:05,921 --> 00:24:08,161
What is that stuff inside them?

467
00:24:09,561 --> 00:24:11,001
Why is everyone fighting over it?

468
00:24:17,041 --> 00:24:18,281
RYAN: Are you sure it's in here?

469
00:24:18,361 --> 00:24:20,321
GRAHAM: I'm not sure about anything.

470
00:24:20,401 --> 00:24:23,121
But this is where the signals
are telling us to go.

471
00:24:25,481 --> 00:24:27,521
RYAN: What do you reckon these are?
GRAHAM: Not a clue.

472
00:24:31,881 --> 00:24:32,881
(BOTH GASP)

473
00:24:32,961 --> 00:24:33,961
(PANTING)

474
00:24:34,801 --> 00:24:36,481
GRAHAM: It's one of Paltraki's crew.

475
00:24:38,121 --> 00:24:39,401
How do we get her out?

476
00:24:40,081 --> 00:24:41,321
We've got to help her.

477
00:24:41,961 --> 00:24:43,361
See if I can find some light.

478
00:24:44,281 --> 00:24:46,001
One of these panels got to do something.

479
00:24:48,121 --> 00:24:49,441
(DEVICES POWERING UP)

480
00:24:49,961 --> 00:24:52,361
-Hey, that's it, you've got it.
-Ryan, look.

481
00:24:53,561 --> 00:24:54,721
(SIGHS)

482
00:24:58,161 --> 00:24:59,561
RYAN: There's more through here.

483
00:25:03,041 --> 00:25:04,321
What do we do?

484
00:25:06,081 --> 00:25:08,201
We only came to rescue two people.

485
00:25:08,921 --> 00:25:10,121
There's dozens in there.

486
00:25:10,401 --> 00:25:11,801
How are we going to get them all out?

487
00:25:15,321 --> 00:25:16,601
(MACHINE THUDDING)

488
00:25:18,281 --> 00:25:19,481
(MACHINE DEPRESSURISING)

489
00:25:28,921 --> 00:25:30,161
You look in a bad way.

490
00:25:30,761 --> 00:25:32,201
Whereas, I've got a new coat.

491
00:25:32,921 --> 00:25:33,921
What do you think?

492
00:25:36,161 --> 00:25:39,601
Ready him. There will be a new target.

493
00:25:41,241 --> 00:25:42,801
DOCTOR: Ready who? For what?

494
00:25:44,441 --> 00:25:46,361
I said, "Ready him."

495
00:25:49,281 --> 00:25:50,601
Whatever the Creator wills.

496
00:25:53,401 --> 00:25:54,481
Out.

497
00:25:58,801 --> 00:26:00,801
Don't worry, I'll look after him.

498
00:26:05,201 --> 00:26:07,681
Tim Shaw. How long has it been?

499
00:26:08,121 --> 00:26:11,921
Three thousand, four hundred
and seven years.

500
00:26:12,961 --> 00:26:14,921
I bet the seven really dragged.

501
00:26:16,401 --> 00:26:17,441
So what happened to you?

502
00:26:22,561 --> 00:26:23,721
(HELMET DEPRESSURISING)

503
00:26:26,681 --> 00:26:28,041
You did.

504
00:26:28,481 --> 00:26:30,601
You corrupted my recall device,

505
00:26:30,681 --> 00:26:34,441
banishing me across the universe
to this desolate rock

506
00:26:34,641 --> 00:26:36,441
for the rest of my existence.

507
00:26:37,001 --> 00:26:39,681
Unable to leave without dying.

508
00:26:41,281 --> 00:26:42,681
This was my curse

509
00:26:43,881 --> 00:26:45,121
for failure.

510
00:26:48,801 --> 00:26:50,361
Or so I thought.

511
00:26:51,281 --> 00:26:53,641
I arrived on the verge of death,

512
00:26:54,001 --> 00:26:55,801
wracked by the DNA bombs.

513
00:26:55,921 --> 00:26:59,081
DOCTOR: But you got more
than you possibly could have wished for.

514
00:26:59,241 --> 00:27:00,441
The Ux.

515
00:27:01,881 --> 00:27:03,881
The universe provides.

516
00:27:05,561 --> 00:27:06,921
You wanted to be a leader.

517
00:27:07,241 --> 00:27:09,441
Now you're worshipped as a false god.

518
00:27:10,561 --> 00:27:12,161
Why all the ships outside?

519
00:27:12,841 --> 00:27:14,081
What have you made them do?

520
00:27:14,161 --> 00:27:15,161
(TZIM-SHA CACKLES)

521
00:27:15,641 --> 00:27:18,241
Do you know what the Ux are capable of?

522
00:27:19,361 --> 00:27:24,121
I carry the entire hive knowledge
of the Stenza civilisation within me.

523
00:27:24,481 --> 00:27:27,841
Paired with the abilities of the Ux.

524
00:27:27,921 --> 00:27:29,881
They were happy to work for me.

525
00:27:30,561 --> 00:27:32,121
Work at what?

526
00:27:32,921 --> 00:27:34,521
(GASPS AND CHOKES)

527
00:27:34,601 --> 00:27:36,041
(ROARS)

528
00:27:36,561 --> 00:27:38,001
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

529
00:27:38,681 --> 00:27:40,721
(HISSING)

530
00:27:41,641 --> 00:27:46,201
What every living creature wishes for.

531
00:27:46,761 --> 00:27:48,041
(SIGHS)

532
00:27:49,441 --> 00:27:50,441
Revenge.

533
00:27:54,361 --> 00:27:55,401
(EXHALES)

534
00:27:55,481 --> 00:27:57,281
Two codebreakers, 30 chambers.

535
00:27:57,521 --> 00:28:00,081
-How much time do you reckon we've got?
-Not enough.

536
00:28:00,601 --> 00:28:03,801
What's bothering me
is how do we know these chambers

537
00:28:03,921 --> 00:28:05,521
aren't set to kill the people
if they're tampered with?

538
00:28:05,601 --> 00:28:07,001
Because you know how sick
that creature is.

539
00:28:07,081 --> 00:28:09,081
It still doesn't give you an excuse
to go after him.

540
00:28:09,601 --> 00:28:12,081
Look at the people in here,
it totally proves my point.

541
00:28:12,201 --> 00:28:14,681
They're trained soldiers
and they couldn't beat him

542
00:28:14,761 --> 00:28:16,441
and you still think you can take him?

543
00:28:16,921 --> 00:28:19,081
Oh, yeah? And why do you care
all of a sudden?

544
00:28:19,921 --> 00:28:22,361
According to you, I was never
good enough for your nan anyway!

545
00:28:22,441 --> 00:28:24,281
I said that a long time ago, Granddad.

546
00:28:24,401 --> 00:28:26,041
Yeah, and I've been waiting
too long for that and all.

547
00:28:26,121 --> 00:28:28,401
Maybe, but you've got it now.

548
00:28:29,681 --> 00:28:30,681
(SIGHS)

549
00:28:31,041 --> 00:28:32,161
We're family

550
00:28:33,761 --> 00:28:34,761
and I love you.

551
00:28:37,601 --> 00:28:39,001
-What did you just say?
-I'm not saying it twice.

552
00:28:39,081 --> 00:28:40,601
Don't pretend you couldn't hear me
the first time.

553
00:28:40,881 --> 00:28:42,801
I'm telling you
what she used to tell me.

554
00:28:43,721 --> 00:28:44,721
Be the better man.

555
00:28:45,481 --> 00:28:46,481
Please.

556
00:28:48,281 --> 00:28:50,321
-(COMPUTER BLEEPING)
-Why is it doing that?

557
00:28:50,601 --> 00:28:51,761
RYAN: Motion detector, maybe.

558
00:28:51,961 --> 00:28:53,881
Do you think the robots shooting
each other set off an alarm?

559
00:28:53,961 --> 00:28:55,001
I don't know.

560
00:29:00,161 --> 00:29:04,201
When you say "revenge,"” revenge on who?

561
00:29:04,601 --> 00:29:06,161
You, Doctor.

562
00:29:07,161 --> 00:29:09,281
Oh, no, don't put this on me.

563
00:29:09,361 --> 00:29:13,641
If you had not interfered
I would have become leader.

564
00:29:14,041 --> 00:29:15,801
First of the Stenza.

565
00:29:17,321 --> 00:29:20,841
And, yet, I should thank you.

566
00:29:21,961 --> 00:29:23,201
Thank me, why?

567
00:29:24,361 --> 00:29:27,321
You have made me a god.

568
00:29:27,441 --> 00:29:29,801
You are nothing of the sort.

569
00:29:31,161 --> 00:29:32,161
(SNARLS)

570
00:29:32,761 --> 00:29:35,721
Now, tell me what this is.

571
00:29:36,201 --> 00:29:38,521
Can't your puny mind understand?

572
00:29:39,401 --> 00:29:40,721
YASMIN: Doctor, we found four more

573
00:29:40,801 --> 00:29:42,641
of those objects.
What do you want us to do?

574
00:29:42,761 --> 00:29:44,481
-(ALARM BLARING)
-DOCTOR: Bit busy at the moment, Yaz.

575
00:29:44,561 --> 00:29:46,361
Someone's coming. Over here.

576
00:29:58,841 --> 00:29:59,961
(DEVICES POWERING UP)

577
00:30:05,081 --> 00:30:06,641
By the Creator's will.

578
00:30:09,481 --> 00:30:12,361
Andinio, please!

579
00:30:13,881 --> 00:30:17,081
Please, don't make me do this again.

580
00:30:17,721 --> 00:30:19,561
We cannot understand the higher plan.

581
00:30:20,961 --> 00:30:22,801
Our faith is all we have.

582
00:30:23,241 --> 00:30:24,241
It's wrong.

583
00:30:24,361 --> 00:30:25,361
DELPH: (GASPS) Please.

584
00:30:25,961 --> 00:30:27,281
This cannot be right!

585
00:30:27,681 --> 00:30:29,121
It'll destroy me.

586
00:30:29,241 --> 00:30:30,681
It'll destroy both of us.

587
00:30:30,761 --> 00:30:32,521
Andinio, please, don't!

588
00:30:34,241 --> 00:30:35,241
(GASPS)

589
00:30:38,721 --> 00:30:39,881
(ENERGY PULSING)

590
00:30:42,681 --> 00:30:43,681
What are they doing?

591
00:30:44,801 --> 00:30:45,801
What's happening?

592
00:30:46,121 --> 00:30:47,481
What did you tell her to do?

593
00:30:48,041 --> 00:30:49,081
Make who ready?

594
00:30:49,161 --> 00:30:51,281
TZIM-SHA: It has taken
thousands of years.

595
00:30:51,481 --> 00:30:55,241
Every fragment of scientific
understanding the Stenza ever possessed

596
00:30:55,841 --> 00:30:58,761
allied to the impossible power
of the Ux.

597
00:30:59,281 --> 00:31:01,001
You will see, Doctor,

598
00:31:01,681 --> 00:31:03,121
I must be a god.

599
00:31:03,441 --> 00:31:05,201
I have the powers of one.

600
00:31:05,761 --> 00:31:08,161
Let me guess, they built you a weapon.

601
00:31:08,521 --> 00:31:10,281
That's what your sort like to do.

602
00:31:10,441 --> 00:31:11,881
Is that why all those ships came?

603
00:31:12,281 --> 00:31:15,041
You made a weapon
and they came to stop you?

604
00:31:15,521 --> 00:31:16,681
Presumably it's here.

605
00:31:17,761 --> 00:31:18,841
Somewhere in this building.

606
00:31:19,641 --> 00:31:22,321
Not in this building, Doctor.

607
00:31:23,321 --> 00:31:26,921
This shrine is the weapon.

608
00:31:30,081 --> 00:31:33,401
The Ux worked so hard to keep me alive.

609
00:31:35,241 --> 00:31:37,201
And they're right to worship me.

610
00:31:37,321 --> 00:31:40,161
I am unstoppable!

611
00:31:41,481 --> 00:31:42,801
No one's unstoppable.

612
00:31:44,841 --> 00:31:47,321
Run, tiny creature.

613
00:31:49,201 --> 00:31:51,601
It will make no difference now.

614
00:31:52,401 --> 00:31:54,081
The weapon is activated, Doctor.

615
00:31:54,841 --> 00:31:57,681
The Stenza held people in stasis
as trophies.

616
00:31:57,761 --> 00:31:59,441
But that was never the goal.

617
00:32:00,921 --> 00:32:04,521
Our ultimate goal
was to hold civilisations.

618
00:32:05,161 --> 00:32:06,641
They never found the way.

619
00:32:07,281 --> 00:32:08,641
But I have.

620
00:32:09,641 --> 00:32:12,441
You gave me my destiny.

621
00:32:13,721 --> 00:32:14,801
(ENERGY WEAPON FIRES)

622
00:32:14,881 --> 00:32:16,761
There, that should
hold them off for a bit.

623
00:32:16,841 --> 00:32:18,521
I hope the Doc's
got everything under control.

624
00:32:18,601 --> 00:32:20,721
I'm not getting a reply.
And we have to get these lot out.

625
00:32:21,281 --> 00:32:22,641
(RUMBLING)

626
00:32:24,001 --> 00:32:25,761
YASMIN: The objects,
why are they shaking?

627
00:32:27,481 --> 00:32:28,921
PALTRAKI: I remember.
DOCTOR: Yaz!

628
00:32:29,081 --> 00:32:30,081
What's happening?

629
00:32:30,241 --> 00:32:31,281
(PANTING) Ooh.

630
00:32:31,601 --> 00:32:32,841
Why are they doing that?

631
00:32:33,201 --> 00:32:34,601
PALTRAKI: I remember what they did.

632
00:32:35,241 --> 00:32:38,201
Five objects, five planets,

633
00:32:38,361 --> 00:32:39,361
one weapon.

634
00:32:39,441 --> 00:32:41,361
They stole five planets.

635
00:32:42,841 --> 00:32:44,081
DOCTOR: Oh, no, no!

636
00:32:46,041 --> 00:32:47,121
That's impossible.

637
00:32:47,441 --> 00:32:48,921
PALTRAKI: It's what happened.

638
00:32:49,001 --> 00:32:51,761
Entire planets removed
from their spatial orbit.

639
00:32:51,841 --> 00:32:52,841
(GASPS)

640
00:32:52,921 --> 00:32:54,481
That would've destroyed all life.

641
00:32:56,281 --> 00:32:57,561
Planetary genocide!

642
00:32:59,801 --> 00:33:03,881
Tim Shaw, I didn't like you then,
but now...

643
00:33:06,201 --> 00:33:07,201
(STATIC)

644
00:33:07,281 --> 00:33:08,321
Make them stop.

645
00:33:08,961 --> 00:33:11,161
You're breaking every known
law of the universe.

646
00:33:11,241 --> 00:33:14,481
I'm rewriting the laws
of the universe.

647
00:33:15,481 --> 00:33:16,521
It doesn't work like that.

648
00:33:16,641 --> 00:33:19,281
TZIM-SHA: Stenza technology
allied to the gift

649
00:33:19,361 --> 00:33:21,641
of the Ux can create anything.

650
00:33:21,761 --> 00:33:23,721
Every action has consequences.

651
00:33:23,961 --> 00:33:26,481
And these are yours, Doctor.

652
00:33:26,561 --> 00:33:27,641
I didn't mean it like that.

653
00:33:27,921 --> 00:33:28,921
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

654
00:33:29,001 --> 00:33:30,001
I'm so annoyed.

655
00:33:30,361 --> 00:33:31,361
The Ux!

656
00:33:33,841 --> 00:33:35,761
They're creating a rift in space-time.

657
00:33:36,361 --> 00:33:38,401
-(ENERGY PULSING)
-He's harnessed their powers.

658
00:33:39,001 --> 00:33:40,001
(WHIRRING)

659
00:33:40,081 --> 00:33:42,001
You don't understand anything right now.

660
00:33:42,081 --> 00:33:45,161
All these planetary masses cannot
exist in the same place

661
00:33:45,241 --> 00:33:47,801
at the same time.
The technology isn't stable.

662
00:33:48,001 --> 00:33:50,601
You bring another through,
it could destroy everything.

663
00:33:50,841 --> 00:33:52,081
TZIM-SHA: You're bluffing.

664
00:33:52,161 --> 00:33:53,161
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

665
00:33:53,241 --> 00:33:55,121
He's one of those people
that really irritates me.

666
00:33:57,081 --> 00:33:58,161
Can we not disconnect them?

667
00:34:00,361 --> 00:34:02,081
He might kill them both if we disrupt it

668
00:34:02,601 --> 00:34:03,761
or destroy this planet.

669
00:34:04,161 --> 00:34:05,641
TZIM-SHA: The target, Doctor,

670
00:34:06,281 --> 00:34:08,681
your responsibility.

671
00:34:09,521 --> 00:34:10,761
You and your friends.

672
00:34:11,121 --> 00:34:12,521
YASMIN: He's targeting Earth!

673
00:34:12,601 --> 00:34:14,521
TZIM-SHA: The site of our first meeting.

674
00:34:14,961 --> 00:34:16,521
Where this war began.

675
00:34:17,721 --> 00:34:22,601
Any world which ever defied or opposed
the Stenza is now my target.

676
00:34:23,881 --> 00:34:27,401
Even in exile, I shall lead.

677
00:34:28,321 --> 00:34:30,961
(LAUGHS) We're in. It worked.

678
00:34:31,401 --> 00:34:33,281
GRAHAM: Hurry up,
I can hear something outside the doors.

679
00:34:34,241 --> 00:34:35,241
(WEAPON COCKS)

680
00:34:43,561 --> 00:34:45,441
Ryan! Come on, son, we haven't got long.

681
00:34:45,761 --> 00:34:47,721
Take my hand. It's okay, you're safe.

682
00:34:49,041 --> 00:34:50,521
It's all right, it's all right.

683
00:34:50,641 --> 00:34:51,961
Chuck us the code breaker, son.

684
00:34:52,921 --> 00:34:53,921
(GRUNTS)

685
00:34:54,161 --> 00:34:55,721
RYAN: We ain't gonna
get them all out in time.

686
00:34:57,681 --> 00:34:59,121
(ALARM BLARING)

687
00:35:00,281 --> 00:35:01,361
(SIGHS)

688
00:35:04,441 --> 00:35:05,721
(SPEAKING INAUDIBLY)

689
00:35:07,801 --> 00:35:08,801
(SNARLS)

690
00:35:09,401 --> 00:35:10,601
(ALARM WAILING)

691
00:35:11,721 --> 00:35:12,921
(CONNECTOR DEPRESSURISING)

692
00:35:13,601 --> 00:35:14,721
(GROANS)

693
00:35:16,081 --> 00:35:17,241
-(GROWLS)
-(CONNECTOR DEPRESSURISING)

694
00:35:18,161 --> 00:35:19,161
(ROARS)

695
00:35:25,481 --> 00:35:27,001
DOCTOR: Can't stop, but must stop it.

696
00:35:27,081 --> 00:35:28,521
GRAHAM: We could do
with some help down here.

697
00:35:28,601 --> 00:35:30,241
Got a few problems of our own, Graham.

698
00:35:30,361 --> 00:35:33,001
I'll go.
This is Paltraki, I'm on my way.

699
00:35:33,081 --> 00:35:34,281
DOCTOR: Get the hostages
back to your ship.

700
00:35:34,361 --> 00:35:35,881
-Yaz, you go with him.
-No.

701
00:35:36,401 --> 00:35:37,921
I'm with you, whatever happens.

702
00:35:38,561 --> 00:35:39,601
We'll wait for you at the ship

703
00:35:39,681 --> 00:35:40,841
for as long as we can.

704
00:35:42,721 --> 00:35:43,881
(COMPUTER BEEPING)

705
00:35:48,161 --> 00:35:49,721
GRAHAM: Everybody, get down,
they're coming through!

706
00:35:54,761 --> 00:35:55,761
(GROANS)

707
00:36:02,201 --> 00:36:04,081
(PANTING)

708
00:36:05,121 --> 00:36:07,241
I still remember
how to take down robots,

709
00:36:07,641 --> 00:36:08,641
luckily for you.

710
00:36:08,881 --> 00:36:11,481
You found my crew. Thank you.

711
00:36:12,521 --> 00:36:13,801
Nice entrance, by the way.

712
00:36:14,201 --> 00:36:15,921
Now, get them back to your ship.

713
00:36:16,161 --> 00:36:17,161
What about you?

714
00:36:17,321 --> 00:36:19,361
-Oh, we've got a couple more to get out.
-Yeah.

715
00:36:19,521 --> 00:36:21,081
GRAHAM: The codebreakers
take a while to work.

716
00:36:24,721 --> 00:36:25,961
You're gonna have company.

717
00:36:26,361 --> 00:36:28,641
Detonate this as they come through
and don't be long.

718
00:36:29,921 --> 00:36:31,641
All right, this way.

719
00:36:34,921 --> 00:36:36,921
The Ux, I've never met a race like them.

720
00:36:37,361 --> 00:36:40,361
They can affect
the shape of the universe by thought.

721
00:36:42,081 --> 00:36:43,241
All that power,

722
00:36:44,401 --> 00:36:45,961
harnessed to Stenza tech.

723
00:36:47,001 --> 00:36:48,921
Can't disconnect them,
it might kill them.

724
00:36:49,681 --> 00:36:51,121
But, if we don't, what happens to Earth?

725
00:36:52,321 --> 00:36:54,681
Their life versus seven billion others.

726
00:36:57,361 --> 00:36:59,361
There must be a way.
There's always a way.

727
00:36:59,441 --> 00:37:00,641
We're really clever.

728
00:37:01,561 --> 00:37:03,121
What have we got? What can we use?

729
00:37:03,321 --> 00:37:05,081
Us versus the Ux. Think.

730
00:37:05,161 --> 00:37:07,321
If they're psychically generating
all this,

731
00:37:07,961 --> 00:37:09,761
I could block the signals.

732
00:37:10,841 --> 00:37:12,001
BOTH: Neural-balancers!

733
00:37:12,601 --> 00:37:15,001
I could adjust the settings really easy,

734
00:37:15,081 --> 00:37:17,121
make them neural-blockers.

735
00:37:17,201 --> 00:37:18,881
No signals out or in.

736
00:37:19,841 --> 00:37:21,481
Could be enough. Big risk.

737
00:37:21,841 --> 00:37:24,521
If we take our balancers off,
put them on those two...

738
00:37:24,601 --> 00:37:26,601
The planet will be able
to attack our minds.

739
00:37:28,161 --> 00:37:31,041
Then I'll take that risk
to stop Earth being destroyed.

740
00:37:31,441 --> 00:37:32,561
Yeah, good.

741
00:37:33,321 --> 00:37:34,721
I mean, really good.

742
00:37:35,001 --> 00:37:37,681
Except it doesn't solve our problem
with these.

743
00:37:37,841 --> 00:37:39,521
They can't all be here.

744
00:37:40,521 --> 00:37:41,961
We have to put them back in place.

745
00:37:42,241 --> 00:37:43,481
It's too many things to do.

746
00:37:43,601 --> 00:37:44,601
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

747
00:37:44,681 --> 00:37:46,241
One thing at a time. It's fine.

748
00:37:47,441 --> 00:37:48,921
All good. Well, almost.

749
00:37:50,481 --> 00:37:51,481
First things first.

750
00:37:52,481 --> 00:37:53,481
-(WHIRRING)
-Ow!

751
00:37:53,801 --> 00:37:54,801
(PANTING)

752
00:37:54,921 --> 00:37:56,721
Take it easy, all right?
There you go.

753
00:37:57,201 --> 00:37:58,321
Ryan, get him out of here!

754
00:37:58,681 --> 00:37:59,961
I will not leave you behind.

755
00:38:00,121 --> 00:38:02,161
I've got to stay here
to time the detonator

756
00:38:02,241 --> 00:38:03,681
to stop them coming after us.

757
00:38:03,761 --> 00:38:04,801
I'll be right behind you.

758
00:38:05,681 --> 00:38:06,681
Promise.

759
00:38:07,041 --> 00:38:08,921
Yeah, yeah, I promise. Go. Go!

760
00:38:09,201 --> 00:38:10,201
Go on!

761
00:38:15,001 --> 00:38:17,161
DOCTOR: Modified neural-balancer on.

762
00:38:17,841 --> 00:38:19,721
Now, you, Yaz, gently does it.

763
00:38:20,241 --> 00:38:21,521
(DEVICE WHIRRING)

764
00:38:23,401 --> 00:38:25,081
Come on, block their signals.

765
00:38:25,681 --> 00:38:27,001
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

766
00:38:36,361 --> 00:38:38,761
No! (PANTING)
What have you done?

767
00:38:38,921 --> 00:38:40,681
This is the Creator's work!

768
00:38:40,841 --> 00:38:41,841
No, it isn't.

769
00:38:41,921 --> 00:38:44,241
That creature took advantage
of your faith.

770
00:38:44,601 --> 00:38:46,521
How could he recognise me, Andinio?

771
00:38:47,561 --> 00:38:48,601
We've met before.

772
00:38:49,001 --> 00:38:51,561
He's an exile from a warrior race
called the Stenza.

773
00:38:51,641 --> 00:38:54,161
When we met, he was killing people
for no reason

774
00:38:54,241 --> 00:38:56,281
on the planet he wants you to destroy.

775
00:38:56,801 --> 00:38:59,281
But the Ux had been waiting for him.

776
00:38:59,601 --> 00:39:00,801
For generations!

777
00:39:01,481 --> 00:39:02,721
He is my truth.

778
00:39:03,481 --> 00:39:05,521
He was our truth.

779
00:39:05,961 --> 00:39:07,441
That creature is a lie.

780
00:39:07,881 --> 00:39:09,841
And he debased you and your faith.

781
00:39:10,361 --> 00:39:12,561
Don't you see, you were the creators!

782
00:39:12,681 --> 00:39:13,881
Look what you can do!

783
00:39:14,161 --> 00:39:15,401
You build.

784
00:39:15,481 --> 00:39:19,441
But he made you destroyers.
That's no god. I'm sorry.

785
00:39:21,361 --> 00:39:23,601
Doctor, something's happening
to the containers.

786
00:39:23,841 --> 00:39:26,121
DOCTOR: Oh, no,
I thought this might happen.

787
00:39:26,721 --> 00:39:29,321
These planets cannot be contained
any longer,

788
00:39:29,441 --> 00:39:30,681
else the damage will be colossal.

789
00:39:36,961 --> 00:39:38,321
Yippee ki-yay, robots.

790
00:39:38,841 --> 00:39:40,281
-(EXPLOSION)
-(GROANS)

791
00:39:43,201 --> 00:39:44,761
Too much to do, not enough time.

792
00:39:45,041 --> 00:39:46,441
Oh, no, that's bad.

793
00:39:47,601 --> 00:39:48,921
The mass is returning.

794
00:39:49,081 --> 00:39:50,281
I can't lift it any more.

795
00:39:51,081 --> 00:39:53,841
But the planets need to be returned
to the exact place in the universe

796
00:39:53,921 --> 00:39:54,921
where they came from.

797
00:39:55,681 --> 00:39:57,961
Can you do it? Can you return them?

798
00:39:59,361 --> 00:40:01,561
-It's possible.
-It would take time.

799
00:40:01,801 --> 00:40:02,801
Which we don't have.

800
00:40:03,001 --> 00:40:04,001
(GROANS)

801
00:40:04,081 --> 00:40:05,281
Oh, my head!

802
00:40:06,281 --> 00:40:07,321
It's getting fuzzy.

803
00:40:07,841 --> 00:40:08,881
-How do we do this?
-Argh!

804
00:40:08,961 --> 00:40:10,001
DOCTOR: What have we got left?

805
00:40:10,401 --> 00:40:12,041
Ooh, one possibility.

806
00:40:12,121 --> 00:40:16,161
(PANTING) You two, this set-up...
Us... What else?

807
00:40:16,281 --> 00:40:17,401
Oh!

808
00:40:19,241 --> 00:40:21,321
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)
-Aligned to Stenza power.

809
00:40:21,721 --> 00:40:23,401
Enough for a short-range dog whistle.

810
00:40:23,921 --> 00:40:25,321
Might work. Please work.

811
00:40:25,961 --> 00:40:27,921
Universe, provide for me.

812
00:40:28,001 --> 00:40:29,441
I'm working really hard
to keep you together

813
00:40:29,521 --> 00:40:30,481
-right now.
-(WHIRRING)

814
00:40:30,561 --> 00:40:32,681
-(WHOOSHING)
-What's that noise?

815
00:40:35,081 --> 00:40:36,521
Tim Shaw might have a shrine,

816
00:40:37,321 --> 00:40:38,921
but I've got a ghost monument.

817
00:40:40,321 --> 00:40:41,881
You can do it. It's not far.

818
00:40:41,961 --> 00:40:43,281
Zero in on my summons.

819
00:40:43,721 --> 00:40:44,641
(METALLIC FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

820
00:40:44,721 --> 00:40:46,001
TZIM-SHA: You should run.

821
00:40:56,481 --> 00:40:57,521
Sorry, Ryan.

822
00:40:59,921 --> 00:41:01,321
(WEAPON POWERING UP)

823
00:41:04,361 --> 00:41:06,241
All right, keep going.
Catch up with them!

824
00:41:09,881 --> 00:41:11,121
(PANTING)

825
00:41:12,121 --> 00:41:13,521
Come on, Graham. Waiting now.

826
00:41:17,041 --> 00:41:18,441
Keep going.

827
00:41:25,121 --> 00:41:26,441
My wife died because of you.

828
00:41:27,641 --> 00:41:28,641
Good.

829
00:41:32,241 --> 00:41:34,201
I swore if I ever saw you again,
I'd kill you.

830
00:41:35,761 --> 00:41:38,081
And yet, you falter.

831
00:41:40,841 --> 00:41:42,241
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRS)
-DOCTOR: Remote summons.

832
00:41:42,321 --> 00:41:44,161
It's locking on. Got it!

833
00:41:46,321 --> 00:41:47,321
What is that?

834
00:41:47,601 --> 00:41:48,601
(PANTING)

835
00:41:48,681 --> 00:41:50,761
You're not the only ones
who can conjure stuff out of nothing.

836
00:41:51,961 --> 00:41:53,761
Do you mind if we get those back?
Bit headachey now.

837
00:41:54,881 --> 00:41:55,881
(NEURAL-BALANCER BUZZES)

838
00:41:56,121 --> 00:41:57,801
Yaz, come on.

839
00:42:05,601 --> 00:42:08,321
Cables, in the portal. Big thick ones.

840
00:42:08,601 --> 00:42:10,641
Drag them out. You and Andinio
loop them into the systems.

841
00:42:10,801 --> 00:42:12,081
-(GROANS)
-DOCTOR: Very fast.

842
00:42:12,401 --> 00:42:13,401
If we can extend

843
00:42:13,481 --> 00:42:14,761
the dematerialisation field

844
00:42:15,281 --> 00:42:16,641
by three metres,

845
00:42:17,041 --> 00:42:18,361
then split the field...

846
00:42:18,641 --> 00:42:20,521
I must be able to split the field.

847
00:42:20,641 --> 00:42:22,361
They're only tiny and I'm clever.

848
00:42:23,481 --> 00:42:24,841
Oi, Ux,

849
00:42:25,121 --> 00:42:26,241
get in here!

850
00:42:29,481 --> 00:42:31,801
DOCTOR: I know this will be
way beyond your comprehension.

851
00:42:32,681 --> 00:42:34,321
Dimensionally transcendental.

852
00:42:34,601 --> 00:42:37,361
Now, get the cables with Yaz
and lock them into the systems.

853
00:42:37,441 --> 00:42:38,521
Delph, come here.

854
00:42:39,041 --> 00:42:40,121
What are you going to do?

855
00:42:40,961 --> 00:42:42,601
Telepathic circuits.

856
00:42:42,681 --> 00:42:45,321
If it can work for your nani's watch,
it can work for that clever lad.

857
00:42:46,681 --> 00:42:48,161
You brought all these things here.

858
00:42:48,441 --> 00:42:50,361
You have all the coordinates
in your head.

859
00:42:50,441 --> 00:42:53,761
The fastest way is to read what's
in your mind and send them back fast,

860
00:42:53,841 --> 00:42:54,961
but keeping us here.

861
00:42:55,041 --> 00:42:56,041
(PANTING)

862
00:42:56,121 --> 00:43:01,201
Their knowledge, their abilities,
Tim Shaw's tech, our blue box.

863
00:43:02,001 --> 00:43:04,201
We'll lash together
every resource we've got.

864
00:43:04,281 --> 00:43:06,881
Sort of like a super group,
best elements of everyone.

865
00:43:06,961 --> 00:43:08,041
(CONSOLE BLEEPS)

866
00:43:08,681 --> 00:43:09,681
Clear?

867
00:43:10,001 --> 00:43:11,121
Not in the least.

868
00:43:11,801 --> 00:43:12,801
Will it work?

869
00:43:12,881 --> 00:43:14,841
No idea, but I once towed your planet

870
00:43:14,921 --> 00:43:16,801
halfway across the universe
with this TARDIS,

871
00:43:16,881 --> 00:43:18,401
and turned a Slitheen back into an eqg.

872
00:43:18,681 --> 00:43:19,841
So, let's give it a go.

873
00:43:20,481 --> 00:43:22,201
(CRACKING)

874
00:43:23,681 --> 00:43:25,041
You are no warrior.

875
00:43:28,041 --> 00:43:29,041
No.

876
00:43:29,121 --> 00:43:31,121
(WEAPON POWERING DOWN)

877
00:43:32,841 --> 00:43:34,121
I'm the better man.

878
00:43:35,321 --> 00:43:36,361
(SNARLS)

879
00:43:37,281 --> 00:43:41,001
-You are weak and feeble.
-RYAN: Tim Shaw,

880
00:43:41,281 --> 00:43:43,561
-don't diss me granddad, ever.
-(TZIM-SHA SNARLS)

881
00:43:44,801 --> 00:43:45,801
(GROANS)

882
00:43:45,961 --> 00:43:47,721
Hey, you shot him!

883
00:43:47,841 --> 00:43:49,281
Yeah, but just the foot.

884
00:43:49,361 --> 00:43:51,401
Just in... Just in the foot.
Just to shut him up.

885
00:43:51,761 --> 00:43:53,521
Ah, don't tell the Doc, she'd be livid.

886
00:43:53,801 --> 00:43:54,961
-(PANTING AND SNARLS)
-(WEAPON POWERING UP)

887
00:43:55,041 --> 00:43:56,121
Shut up!

888
00:43:56,801 --> 00:43:57,961
And stop with that hand thing.

889
00:43:58,801 --> 00:44:00,281
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

890
00:44:06,681 --> 00:44:07,681
What do we do now?

891
00:44:08,761 --> 00:44:10,241
DOCTOR: I know this will be painful.

892
00:44:10,641 --> 00:44:11,641
I wouldn't put you through this

893
00:44:11,721 --> 00:44:13,201
if I could think
of any other way right now.

894
00:44:13,521 --> 00:44:15,121
-It's okay.
-DOCTOR: It's not.

895
00:44:15,361 --> 00:44:16,361
But thank you.

896
00:44:18,361 --> 00:44:19,361
Ready?

897
00:44:20,001 --> 00:44:23,201
ANDINIO: May the will
of the true Creator give me strength.

898
00:44:26,601 --> 00:44:27,601
Ready!

899
00:44:28,521 --> 00:44:29,721
-(EXPLOSION)
-(SCREAMS)

900
00:44:31,041 --> 00:44:32,241
-(DELPH SCREAMING)
-Please, please, please,

901
00:44:32,321 --> 00:44:33,601
no back-up plan.

902
00:44:36,241 --> 00:44:37,401
(YELPS)

903
00:44:38,001 --> 00:44:39,081
I'm sorry, Delph.

904
00:44:40,281 --> 00:44:41,561
(STRAINING)

905
00:44:44,001 --> 00:44:45,001
(SCREAMING)

906
00:44:49,041 --> 00:44:50,361
YASMIN: Stay strong, Andinio.

907
00:44:51,041 --> 00:44:53,121
ANDINIO: Our faith
will survive deception.

908
00:44:53,201 --> 00:44:54,721
My service to the creator

909
00:44:54,801 --> 00:44:56,081
must never be known.

910
00:44:56,281 --> 00:44:57,361
It's working!

911
00:44:57,721 --> 00:44:58,721
Possibly.

912
00:44:58,841 --> 00:45:00,081
-(DELPH SCREAMING)
-Just hold...

913
00:45:00,681 --> 00:45:02,201
Keep at it, all of you!

914
00:45:02,561 --> 00:45:03,721
ANDINIO: We are the Ux.

915
00:45:03,841 --> 00:45:05,441
We are the blessed two.

916
00:45:05,521 --> 00:45:08,041
Our faith wins. Our faith restores.

917
00:45:15,521 --> 00:45:17,321
(SCREAMING)

918
00:45:26,841 --> 00:45:28,001
(GASPS)

919
00:45:28,081 --> 00:45:29,081
(SIGHS)

920
00:45:29,161 --> 00:45:30,281
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

921
00:45:30,961 --> 00:45:32,961
-(SIGHS)
-DOCTOR: Delph.

922
00:45:41,241 --> 00:45:42,521
GRAHAM: You brought us all together.

923
00:45:42,961 --> 00:45:44,481
You ain't gonna tear us apart.

924
00:45:45,121 --> 00:45:46,321
You ain't worth killing.

925
00:45:47,721 --> 00:45:49,481
But you can have a taste
of your own medicine.

926
00:45:50,121 --> 00:45:52,401
We're not weak, we're strong

927
00:45:53,121 --> 00:45:55,921
and we sentence you to life.

928
00:45:58,681 --> 00:46:01,041
So, as you're contemplating eternity,

929
00:46:01,521 --> 00:46:03,121
keep one name on your mind.

930
00:46:05,121 --> 00:46:06,241
BOTH: Grace.

931
00:46:08,801 --> 00:46:10,321
(TZIM-SHA GROWLING)

932
00:46:19,201 --> 00:46:21,161
(GROWLS)

933
00:46:25,201 --> 00:46:26,361
(PANTING)

934
00:46:26,681 --> 00:46:28,001
You did it!

935
00:46:28,601 --> 00:46:29,641
You did it, Delph!

936
00:46:29,721 --> 00:46:31,241
Oh, did... Did it work?

937
00:46:31,721 --> 00:46:33,801
You are a couple of awesome Ux.

938
00:46:34,001 --> 00:46:35,001
Thank you.

939
00:46:35,441 --> 00:46:38,121
Praise the true Creator's will.

940
00:46:38,401 --> 00:46:39,601
We are the blessed few.

941
00:46:41,121 --> 00:46:42,121
(DOOR OPENING)

942
00:46:46,201 --> 00:46:47,241
(CHUCKLES)

943
00:46:47,321 --> 00:46:48,961
You ain't half made a mess in here.

944
00:46:51,121 --> 00:46:52,121
Where's Tim Shaw?

945
00:46:53,121 --> 00:46:56,081
Oh, he's taking a very long nap
in a very small stasis chamber.

946
00:46:56,161 --> 00:46:57,281
Of his own making.

947
00:46:57,681 --> 00:46:59,001
-I like that. (CHUCKLES)
-Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

948
00:47:01,201 --> 00:47:02,201
Oh, I couldn't do it, Doc.

949
00:47:02,281 --> 00:47:04,881
Yeah, I had the chance... Too weak.

950
00:47:06,521 --> 00:47:09,721
Graham O'Brien,
you're the strongest person I know.

951
00:47:10,601 --> 00:47:12,881
Well, one of a few.

952
00:47:15,921 --> 00:47:17,561
(WIND HOWLING)

953
00:47:21,041 --> 00:47:22,241
PALTRAKI: What about that creature?

954
00:47:22,961 --> 00:47:25,201
ANDINIO: We sealed the building
as we left.

955
00:47:25,801 --> 00:47:27,161
No one can get to him.

956
00:47:28,361 --> 00:47:29,921
I'm sorry for the way he betrayed you.

957
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:35,481
We can take these people home,
save you the job.

958
00:47:36,081 --> 00:47:38,521
No, I'm going to complete my mission.

959
00:47:40,761 --> 00:47:42,921
-Then take us, too.
-Delph.

960
00:47:43,721 --> 00:47:46,841
This is our home. We must stay here.

961
00:47:47,281 --> 00:47:48,281
No.

962
00:47:49,321 --> 00:47:51,281
We need to understand what's out there.

963
00:47:54,161 --> 00:47:55,201
Find another home.

964
00:47:57,481 --> 00:47:59,121
You'll have to sleep on the floor.

965
00:47:59,481 --> 00:48:01,321
I walked this planet for decades.

966
00:48:02,001 --> 00:48:03,081
Floors are fine.

967
00:48:05,521 --> 00:48:06,521
(INHALES SHARPLY)

968
00:48:06,801 --> 00:48:08,321
Where will you go, now?

969
00:48:10,081 --> 00:48:11,761
(EXHALES SHARPLY) No idea.

970
00:48:13,401 --> 00:48:14,401
Come on, fam.

971
00:48:15,001 --> 00:48:16,561
I thought we weren't doing "fam."

972
00:48:17,441 --> 00:48:18,441
I like it.

973
00:48:25,281 --> 00:48:27,041
None of us know for sure
what's out there.

974
00:48:27,881 --> 00:48:29,121
That's why we keep looking.

975
00:48:30,561 --> 00:48:31,561
Keep your faith.

976
00:48:33,401 --> 00:48:34,601
Travel hopefully.

977
00:48:35,401 --> 00:48:36,801
The universe will surprise you.

978
00:48:38,361 --> 00:48:39,361
Constantly.

979
00:48:45,441 --> 00:48:46,441
(CREAKING)

980
00:48:50,321 --> 00:48:53,121
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

981
00:48:58,521 --> 00:49:00,521
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

982
00:49:32,001 --> 00:49:34,241
Here's a new year message
for you to send...

983
00:49:34,321 --> 00:49:38,241
Earth is protected by me and my mates
this year and every other.

